## Git Workflow

- **Always create feature branches** (never commit directly to main)
- Branch naming: `feature/<issue-number>-<short-description>`
- Commit messages: `<type>: <description>` (feat/fix/docs/refactor)
- Reference GitHub issues in commits: `Fixes #42`

### Git Pager (Avoid Interactive `less`)

Some git commands page output via `less`, which looks like a “stuck menu” and requires `q` to exit. To keep all git commands non-interactive in this repo:

- Prefer `git --no-pager <command>` for any command that could produce long output.
- Or use `git -c core.pager=cat <command>` to override the pager for a single command.
- Avoid running `git log`, `git diff`, `git show`, etc. without one of the above flags unless output is known to be short.

